The paper focuses on designing legged robots with desired behaviors and morphologies using an interactive computational design system. This involves optimization techniques that reason about the structure and motion of the robot to achieve user-specified behavior and performance. This work is closely related to robotics (cs.RO), as it deals with designing legged robots. It also involves optimization techniques (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to achieve user-specified behavior. Additionally, the paper mentions using simulation to evaluate the system, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
